1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:02,340
Mom, am I Ok Hee,

2
00:00:03,140 --> 00:00:04,710
and my sister is Tok Hee?

3
00:00:05,540 --> 00:00:07,110
Is that why...

4
00:00:07,210 --> 00:00:09,110
you've been calling the bunnies
Ok Hee and Tok Hee?

5
00:00:09,450 --> 00:00:11,450
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are sleeping.

6
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:15,190
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

7
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:17,560
Jang Mi is so pretty.

8
00:00:19,090 --> 00:00:21,030
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are so pretty.

9
00:00:23,290 --> 00:00:24,300
Jang Mi.

10
00:00:25,730 --> 00:00:26,830
Listen to me carefully.

11
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:30,640
The one who did that to your mother...

12
00:00:32,670 --> 00:00:33,770
and you...

13
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:35,910
You...

14
00:00:38,010 --> 00:00:39,010
Ssangkal...

15
00:00:40,650 --> 00:00:43,750
Dad was trying to tell me I have a twin.

16
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,620
He was trying to tell me I have a twin
even in his final moments.

17
00:00:49,890 --> 00:00:51,560
Does the person who did this to Mom...

18
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:54,660
have something to do
with me having a twin?

19
00:01:07,410 --> 00:01:08,410
Seo Rin.

20
00:01:08,810 --> 00:01:12,240
No, Seo Rin has to be my twin.

21
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:14,910
Dad must have run into Seo Rin somewhere.

22
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:15,910
And...

23
00:01:16,550 --> 00:01:19,420
he must have known who was responsible
for what happened to Mom.

24
00:01:19,980 --> 00:01:22,820
We'll see each other again.

25
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:25,660
But you need to wait quietly until then.

26
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:28,630
And don't say a word about this to anyone.

27
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:30,160
Got it?

28
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,100
Promise me.

29
00:01:32,730 --> 00:01:34,370
It's the only way
we'll see each other again.

30
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:37,640
She told me not to tell anyone about this.

31
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,370
Seo Rin must know something.

32
00:01:42,610 --> 00:01:44,140
So then, how much does she know?

33
00:01:55,690 --> 00:01:57,660
- You wanted to see me?
- Yes, General Manager Kang.

34
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:59,020
Come and have a seat.

35
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:03,660
General Manager Kang.

36
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:06,230
The meeting was a huge success,

37
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:09,070
and the Chairman and the board
are all very pleased.

38
00:02:10,270 --> 00:02:12,940
So, with that said,
are you free this evening?

39
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:17,080
I thought we could drive out of the city
and have dinner with Seo Rin.

40
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:19,810
Perfect! Let's all go, okay?

41
00:02:19,810 --> 00:02:21,510
I'm sorry, but you two should go ahead.

42
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:23,980
I have a family get-together tonight.

43
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:28,820
- A family gathering?
- Yes, we haven't all met up in a while.

44
00:02:28,950 --> 00:02:32,190
Oh my, Jun Ho, I didn't know
you were such a family man.

45
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:35,160
Such a cool, aloof guy
is also a family man.

46
00:02:35,790 --> 00:02:37,330
Quite the surprising twist. I like it.

47
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:40,730
Director Ma, you seem to be
back to your old self.

48
00:02:41,270 --> 00:02:43,370
You seemed out of it
for the past few days.

49
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:45,100
I did?

50
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:47,470
Wow.

51
00:02:47,810 --> 00:02:50,280
Looks like you've been watching me
very closely, Jun Ho.

52
00:02:50,610 --> 00:02:52,910
That's proof that you're interested in me,
isn't it?

53
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,110
Mom, this is a good sign, right?

54
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:57,450
Jun Ho.

55
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:01,450
You act cold, but you really do like me.
Don't you?

56
00:03:01,450 --> 00:03:04,120
If that's everything, I'll see myself out.

57
00:03:09,660 --> 00:03:12,730
Stop getting distracted
and focus on General Manager Kang.

58
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:16,230
Speaking of which, General Manager Kang
seems to be very interested in pottery.

59
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:18,570
He'd love it if I made something
for him, right?

60
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,410
I'm leaving, then.

61
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:31,550
Manager Lee.

62
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:33,690
I need you to tail Seo Rin.

63
00:03:34,550 --> 00:03:36,720
So you want to start lessons tomorrow?

64
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:40,090
- Yes, I can come in anytime, right?
- Of course.

65
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:42,730
By the way, is there another exit?

66
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:44,500
It's over there.

67
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:46,700
I see.

68
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:50,300
Dad, about the day of your accident,

69
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,900
you said you were heading out
because of your students' grades,

70
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:55,110
but why did you end up so far away
when the accident happened?

71
00:03:57,480 --> 00:04:01,980
- Well...
- That's right. I was wondering that too.

72
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:05,480
I kept meaning to ask you,
but I never got around to it.

73
00:04:05,780 --> 00:04:08,050
I was on my way to the school
about the students' grades,

74
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,560
but something urgent came up
with a project with Dream Hotel,

75
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:12,360
so I was heading toward
the resort instead.

76
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:13,990
A project with Dream Hotel?

77
00:04:14,260 --> 00:04:15,260
That's right.

78
00:04:15,330 --> 00:04:18,460
So you were supposed to meet CEO Chae
at the resort, too?

79
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:19,800
CEO Chae Hwa Young?

80
00:04:20,130 --> 00:04:24,470
Why would someone as busy as CEO Chae
go there in the middle of the night?

81
00:04:24,870 --> 00:04:28,170
I was going alone to check on something
at the resort, and then it happened.

82
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:32,310
I think I need to meet with CEO Chae.

83
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,650
Why would you go meet someone
as busy as CEO Chae? What for?

84
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:38,780
Regarding your accident,
he has a reason to see her.

85
00:04:38,780 --> 00:04:41,090
Why are you so worked up, honey?

86
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:45,920
I feel bad enough for all the trouble
I've caused her.

87
00:04:46,460 --> 00:04:48,730
Baek Ho doesn't need to go
bother her as well.

88
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:51,660
No, it's just that something feels off.

89
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,330
I'll make sure it doesn't cause you
any trouble, Dad.

90
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:00,170
Baek Ho isn't a child anymore.

91
00:05:00,570 --> 00:05:03,880
Why are you so worried?

92
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:12,950
One, two, three!

93
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:13,950
- A hippo?
- A hippo?

94
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:15,320
You two are a real couple!

95
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:17,460
Congratulations!

96
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,560
This is amazing!

97
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,800
I wonder
if Jang Mi is thinking of me, too.

98
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:29,270
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

99
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,310
I wonder if the person
who took Seo Rin away...

100
00:05:35,910 --> 00:05:37,910
is somehow connected to my dad's death.

101
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:42,210
But how did he end up dying
in Baek Ho's father's car?

102
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,850
I have so many questions.

103
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:49,450
I don't have Seo Rin's contact info.
I really need to see her.

104
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:54,930
Seo Rin, please call me. Okay?

105
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:00,160
What?

106
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,500
(Restricted Number)

107
00:06:04,170 --> 00:06:05,170
Hello?

108
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,810
Seo Rin!

109
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:11,010
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

110
00:06:11,110 --> 00:06:12,110
A pottery studio?

111
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:18,420
She said she was making a plate
for General Manager Kang.

112
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:20,420
I guess that's why she went to the studio.

113
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:23,490
Got it. Pull back.

114
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:27,760
Manager Lee, book a tee time.

115
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:29,760
You're planning to play a round?

116
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,630
If I want to...

117
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:35,330
get Jun Ho settled in at Dream,
I'll have to do some legwork, right?

118
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,900
It seems the resort would be best
for General Manager Kang to make his mark.

119
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:40,200
Exactly.

120
00:06:51,450 --> 00:06:53,320
So we finally meet.

121
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:57,360
I can't believe I'm actually seeing you.

122
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:00,530
Judging by how casually
you're talking to me,

123
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,430
I guess you've figured out we're twins.

124
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:04,930
When did you find out?

125
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,130
If you knew, why did you feed me that line
about being doppelgangers?

126
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:10,640
Why? Tell me.

127
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,040
Because I knew you'd be like this.

128
00:07:12,670 --> 00:07:14,440
I knew you'd bombard me with questions.

129
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,080
We're a spitting image of each other.

130
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:21,080
It really feels like
I'm looking in a mirror.

131
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:24,620
Even for twins,
how can we look so identical?

132
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:26,050
Shit.

133
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:30,250
My mom always used to say,
"Ok Hee and Tok Hee."

134
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:33,220
I thought it was some baby nickname.

135
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:35,190
I realized I was Ok Hee,

136
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:37,400
and you were Tok Hee.

137
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,330
That's why
she always said them together as a set.

138
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:42,770
I had no idea.

139
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:48,510
Okay, so what?

140
00:07:49,210 --> 00:07:51,480
Seo Rin, who are you really?

141
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:53,480
Who's your mother?

142
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:55,980
How did you end up living
with a different family?

143
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,480
If I can find out who raised you,

144
00:07:58,980 --> 00:08:02,920
maybe that person has something to do
with my mom's accident...

145
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,660
and maybe with even Dad's death.

146
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:11,330
Even twins must have
some differences, right?

147
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,730
Seo Rin, are you listening to me?

148
00:08:14,170 --> 00:08:17,070
Aren't you curious about
why we were separated?

149
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,700
I'm not.

150
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,070
I'm not curious.

151
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:23,980
How can you not be curious?

152
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:26,140
Open your eyes
and take a good look at yourself.

153
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:30,010
You seem to be dirt poor.

154
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:33,990
But I'm so rich, I have more money
than I know what to do with.

155
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:37,820
So what's the point of digging up
why we were separated now?

156
00:08:37,890 --> 00:08:39,090
Hey, Seo Rin!

157
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:42,430
Your parents have nothing to do with me.

158
00:08:42,430 --> 00:08:43,460
You know?

159
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:47,770
And I'm so glad we were separated.

160
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,000
Otherwise,
I would've ended up living like you.

161
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:53,740
I really don't get you at all.

162
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:57,210
Don't you want to see your birth mother?
Aren't you curious about her?

163
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,280
Oh Jang Mi.

164
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:00,980
You really are hopelessly old-fashioned
and naive.

165
00:09:01,410 --> 00:09:04,280
- So what if your mom gave birth to me?
- Hey, Seo Rin!

166
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:08,150
I don't know
what kind of pampered life you're living,

167
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:10,050
but don't you dare
turn away from the truth.

168
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:11,120
Shit.

169
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:12,390
This is boring.

170
00:09:13,260 --> 00:09:15,290
I've already got enough stress
to deal with,

171
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:17,460
and I thought meeting you would be fun.

172
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:18,460
But no.

173
00:09:18,530 --> 00:09:19,530
I was wrong.

174
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,200
Shit.

175
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:24,240
- Don't contact me again.
- Seo Rin.

176
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,600
Fine.

177
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:29,070
We spent ten months together
in our mom's womb.

178
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,680
This is the first time
we've seen each other in decades.

179
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:33,580
We can't just end it like this.

180
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:38,520
First, I need to calm her down
and get her on my side.

181
00:09:39,050 --> 00:09:42,320
It must be a huge shock for her, too,

182
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,850
that her parents aren't really her own.

183
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,560
Let's go.

184
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:51,830
- What?
- I wanted to do this with a friend.

185
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:53,460
Let's go do that.

186
00:09:54,230 --> 00:09:56,000
Do what?

187
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:18,460
I guess you have good eyesight.
I wear glasses.

188
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:22,190
I got LASEK, of course.
That was almost ten years ago.

189
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:25,060
Go on, try some.

190
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,900
You said you wanted to try malatang.

191
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,400
All right.

192
00:10:35,410 --> 00:10:36,410
It's spicy.

193
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,440
You're a lightweight
when it comes to spicy food.

194
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,030
Hey.

195
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:01,970
Going shopping, grabbing a bite,

196
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:03,870
getting manicures, getting massages...

197
00:11:03,870 --> 00:11:05,670
You wanted to do all this with a friend?

198
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:06,940
Lie still.

199
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:09,440
- The manager gets mad if they fall.
- Okay.

200
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:14,450
- You don't have any friends?
- I lived abroad for a long time.

201
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,380
I haven't been back
in Korea for very long.

202
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:19,220
So? Feeling a bit more relaxed?

203
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:23,890
I'm not relaxed at all.

204
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:28,990
- My life feels like a roller coaster.
- A roller coaster?

205
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:33,360
Sounds like you have an exciting life.
People pay money to ride those.

206
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:38,340
- You think my life is fun?
- I'm bored to death.

207
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,600
Shit.

208
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:44,840
- How about we trade lives?
- Okay, let's do it.

209
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:48,350
Oh Jang Mi, I don't want to.

210
00:11:48,650 --> 00:11:51,450
I don't want to live
a pathetic life like yours.

211
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,780
Hey, Seo Rin.

212
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:58,490
Look, I don't have time
to be messing around with you like this.

213
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:00,660
I have to find out who hurt our mom...

214
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:03,560
and catch whoever's behind my dad's death.

215
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,360
And the key is the person
who took you away.

216
00:12:06,730 --> 00:12:09,270
So tell me. Who's your mother?

217
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,340
Who is your family?

218
00:12:22,410 --> 00:12:26,550
She should be grateful
I stole her and not Oh Jang Mi.

219
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:29,450
I'm the one
who lets her live like a princess.

220
00:12:30,150 --> 00:12:33,360
If I had taken Oh Jang Mi instead of her,

221
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:35,560
she'd be the one suffering...

222
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,330
as Jung Suk Hee's daughter
right now, right?

223
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:40,130
I don't have time
to be messing around with you either.

224
00:12:40,630 --> 00:12:43,000
I'm spending this time with you
to make up my mind.

225
00:12:43,770 --> 00:12:46,540
Whether I should dump
my mother on you or not.

226
00:12:46,970 --> 00:12:49,670
Hey, Seo Rin.
Are you really not going to tell me?

227
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:55,750
Minister. This is Chae Hwa Young.

228
00:12:57,620 --> 00:12:59,780
I know it's been a while, hasn't it?

229
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:03,750
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

230
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,390
I'd like to treat you sometime,

231
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,690
Minister, how's your schedule
looking these days?

232
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:11,700
Why did CEO Chae pull her support?

233
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,230
Could there have been a misunderstanding?

234
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:23,870
The person you're calling is unavailable.
Connecting to voicemail.

235
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:26,440
- She's not picking up.
- Charges will apply after the beep.

236
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:29,050
Tae Pyung.

237
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:34,120
You're not welcome here.

238
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:36,320
I told you to stay out of my sight.

239
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:43,860
Did you...

240
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,830
go to my father's accident scene again?

241
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,700
Yes.

242
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,840
Just in case I missed any evidence.

243
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:56,010
I heard you go all the way
out there every day.

244
00:13:56,770 --> 00:13:57,780
So it was true.

245
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:01,010
I really liked your father.

246
00:14:01,910 --> 00:14:03,280
And I respected him.

247
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:05,920
I will do whatever it takes...

248
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:07,620
to get to the bottom
of your father's death.

249
00:14:11,860 --> 00:14:12,890
Thanks.

250
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,530
What?

251
00:14:15,890 --> 00:14:17,230
I said, thanks.

252
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:19,630
And...

253
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:21,500
for everything,

254
00:14:22,130 --> 00:14:23,200
I'm sorry.

255
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,570
What's there to be sorry about
between friends?

256
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:34,410
Hong Ju, great news!

257
00:14:34,550 --> 00:14:37,680
What is it?
Isn't this a little too much good news?

258
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:38,920
Hey, listen.

259
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:43,090
I'm finally getting married!

260
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:46,460
- Really?
- That's right.

261
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:48,660
Can you believe it?

262
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:52,730
I guess I'm really going to be
the Chairman's wife.

263
00:14:53,460 --> 00:14:55,430
So you're really going through
with the wedding?

264
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:58,440
My gosh, does that mean we'll officially
go on his family registry?

265
00:14:58,540 --> 00:15:00,300
I don't know about that yet.

266
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:03,440
But a journey of a thousand miles
begins with a single step, right?

267
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:05,310
Once he and I go through the ceremony
and take the photos,

268
00:15:05,310 --> 00:15:06,780
our common-law marriage
will be set in stone.

269
00:15:07,010 --> 00:15:09,110
And the next step
is getting on the family registry.

270
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:14,150
Once he and I have the ceremony,
we're halfway there.

271
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:16,890
- Mrs. Yeom, where are you?
- Oh my.

272
00:15:16,890 --> 00:15:18,820
I'm coming!

273
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:20,920
The Chairman...

274
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:23,930
I mean, my husband is looking for me.

275
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:26,530
Then, shouldn't we go to a salon
before the wedding ceremony?

276
00:15:27,930 --> 00:15:29,670
What? She already hung up on me.

277
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,870
- Ma'am...
- What did I just hear?

278
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:36,170
Ma'am.

279
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:38,780
Your mother is going through
with a wedding with my father-in-law?

280
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:41,450
I just found out myself.

281
00:15:43,950 --> 00:15:45,550
- Come on, just try it like this.
- Stop it.

282
00:15:45,780 --> 00:15:48,490
It's enough for you to do it, Mrs. Yeom.
I don't see why I have to.

283
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:51,220
What do you mean, you don't have to?

284
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:53,820
You're the groom, Chairman.

285
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,890
If you want to stand next to me
in my wedding dress,

286
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:59,160
- you have to look a little younger.
- Stop it.

287
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:01,900
Okay.

288
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:04,370
By the way, Chairman.

289
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:08,810
Why the sudden rush to have the wedding?

290
00:16:09,370 --> 00:16:12,780
We can hold it at our hotel, of course,

291
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:16,280
- but if we want to invite our friends...
- Why would we invite anyone?

292
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:19,020
- What?
- It's pointless and unbecoming.

293
00:16:19,350 --> 00:16:21,650
Why would we call everyone
to brag about this at my age?

294
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:25,790
Let me make myself clear.
Don't you say a word about this to anyone.

295
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:29,290
It's just a formality.
There's no need to make a fuss.

296
00:16:29,690 --> 00:16:32,100
We'll just snap a picture
and be done with it.

297
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:34,830
I understand.

298
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:39,540
There's my sweet girl.
Are you just getting home?

299
00:16:44,110 --> 00:16:47,580
Oh my goodness.
She just ignored you completely.

300
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:49,750
What's gotten into her lately, Chairman?

301
00:16:51,380 --> 00:16:55,120
Is this her way
of protesting our marriage?

302
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,190
Hello, CEO Chae. It's me.

303
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:10,470
Baek Ho? What are you doing here?

304
00:17:10,670 --> 00:17:13,270
Are you playing dumb again?
Why do you think I'm here?

305
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:14,440
I was waiting for you, of course.

306
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:17,570
Hold on, you've got something right there.

307
00:17:40,730 --> 00:17:42,230
Jang Mi is so pretty.

308
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,340
Hello. You're here.

309
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:48,510
Mom, you're here?

310
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,810
I guess you were home.

311
00:17:52,010 --> 00:17:54,910
Jang Mi and Baek Ho are kissing.

312
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:59,550
- Well, that's...
- No, Mom. Why would he and I...

313
00:17:59,650 --> 00:18:01,520
No, Mom. You must have seen it wrong.

314
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:03,890
But I saw you.

315
00:18:06,290 --> 00:18:08,530
- What are you smiling at?
- Nothing.

316
00:18:08,790 --> 00:18:13,200
It's just that you look so pretty.
Your skin is glowing today.

317
00:18:16,100 --> 00:18:19,700
Jang Mi is pretty.
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

318
00:18:22,270 --> 00:18:24,940
Mom, I met Tok Hee.

319
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:26,810
Your daughter, Tok Hee.

320
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:30,010
I'm going to bring Seo Rin back,
no matter what.

321
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:32,650
I'll make sure to bring
your daughter, Seo Rin, here,

322
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:34,280
so you can see her.

323
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:36,350
So, where have you been?

324
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:39,360
What?

325
00:18:40,690 --> 00:18:42,130
I'll tell you later.

326
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:47,100
Seo Rin.

327
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:51,140
Isn't it nice having the whole family
together for breakfast like this?

328
00:18:53,370 --> 00:18:55,610
Good. I'm glad you came.

329
00:18:56,610 --> 00:19:00,380
So you cut your nails
because you're taking up pottery?

330
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:05,680
Seo Rin is not only a hard worker,
but her dedication is admirable, Father.

331
00:19:05,780 --> 00:19:09,220
As she should be.
She is my successor, after all.

332
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:13,990
Honey, with Seo Rin and Hong Ju...

333
00:19:14,190 --> 00:19:17,330
acting as your loyal guardians,

334
00:19:17,430 --> 00:19:19,560
you must feel unstoppable.

335
00:19:21,230 --> 00:19:24,100
Father, please have some of this.

336
00:19:24,370 --> 00:19:25,570
Thank you.

337
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,840
- You eat up too.
- Shit, Jin Hong Ju.

338
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:31,640
Stop with the fake sweet act.
It's nauseating.

339
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:34,210
By the way, I heard Professor Kang,

340
00:19:34,210 --> 00:19:37,610
who worked with CEO Chae
on a project with Dream Resort,

341
00:19:37,610 --> 00:19:39,520
got into trouble. Is that true?

342
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:45,060
I'm just worried it might cause
problems for your work, honey.

343
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:48,560
Isn't that why the police came to see you
the other day, ma'am?

344
00:19:48,830 --> 00:19:49,990
Yeom San Wol.

345
00:19:50,330 --> 00:19:52,500
This is hardly the time or place
for this conversation.

346
00:19:54,230 --> 00:19:57,130
But I heard the person
Professor Kang ran over and killed...

347
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:59,800
went to see you before he died, CEO Chae.

348
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,510
Who was it?

349
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:03,240
My goodness.

350
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:06,180
How is it that everyone you know...

351
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:08,980
ends up either killing someone
or getting killed?

352
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:11,150
Wow.

353
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:13,350
Yeom San Wol.

354
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:15,920
You're saying all this on purpose
for Father to hear, aren't you?

355
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:19,220
And you think this is
appropriate breakfast conversation?

356
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:22,760
If you have so little discretion,

357
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:26,930
I really don't see how you can
support the Chairman.

358
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:30,600
What makes you say I have no discretion,
my dear daughter-in-law?

359
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:34,270
Do you really think that's appropriate
for the breakfast table?

360
00:20:34,940 --> 00:20:36,870
It's enough to make anyone
lose their appetite.

361
00:20:36,940 --> 00:20:39,340
That's enough.
No need to get so worked up.

362
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:43,580
Besides, it sounds like
it was just a simple car accident.

363
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:48,150
And dragging CEO Chae into it seems like
baseless speculation, Mrs. Yeom.

364
00:20:48,220 --> 00:20:50,820
Oh my. Was I?

365
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:52,390
I was simply...

366
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:56,130
You're so excited about the wedding
you can't control your mouth.

367
00:20:57,090 --> 00:21:01,060
You'll need to calm down if you want
your bridal makeup to look good, San Wol.

368
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:04,130
CEO Chae, you'd better watch your words
from now on as well.

369
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:07,040
And don't just call her "San Wol"
at the end of every sentence.

370
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:10,310
Treat her with the respect
my partner deserves.

371
00:21:12,310 --> 00:21:13,710
Yes, Father.

372
00:21:15,580 --> 00:21:16,910
Honey.

373
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:20,280
Thank you.

374
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:33,630
I wonder if Oh Jang Mi has this mole too.

375
00:21:39,370 --> 00:21:42,810
- It's almost time for the ceremony.
- Right. Let's go.

376
00:21:48,110 --> 00:21:50,180
Excuse me, do you happen to
recognize this person?

377
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:51,550
I don't think so.

378
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,680
He's pretty tall.

379
00:21:55,220 --> 00:21:58,720
- No, I really don't know. Sorry.
- Please, could you take another look?

380
00:21:58,820 --> 00:22:01,390
He's pretty tall. Around five-foot-eleven?

381
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:03,630
I don't recall anyone that tall.

382
00:22:04,260 --> 00:22:06,130
He would have been carrying a lunchbox.

383
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:07,560
Someone like that...

384
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:08,700
Yes, I'm Kang Baek Ho.

385
00:22:10,670 --> 00:22:12,670
- Excuse me, but...
- I'm Ma Seo Rin.

386
00:22:12,770 --> 00:22:15,470
I'm the Director of Food and Beverage.

387
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:21,140
Kang Baek Ho has met my Seo Rin before.

388
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:23,380
We should go, Ma'am.

389
00:22:23,650 --> 00:22:24,680
Manager Lee.

390
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:27,780
I can't let Kang Baek Ho run into Seo Rin.

391
00:22:28,490 --> 00:22:29,690
Get him out of here now.

392
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:32,520
Yes, ma'am.

393
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:43,400
Hello.

394
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:53,640
Okay.

395
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,810
Jun Ho. Hi.

396
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:09,490
Manager Lee.

397
00:23:09,490 --> 00:23:12,130
I can't let Kang Baek Ho run into Seo Rin.

398
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,130
Get him out of here now.

399
00:23:14,630 --> 00:23:16,400
Kang Baek Ho is here at the hotel?

400
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,300
I'm just going to the restroom.

401
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:26,010
Where do you think you're going?

402
00:23:26,580 --> 00:23:27,610
To the restroom.

403
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:29,380
Go later.

404
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,630
What is this?

405
00:23:50,970 --> 00:23:54,500
Please, agree to a settlement
for my husband's case.

406
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:58,040
I've made sure it's a generous offer.

407
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:00,140
- A settlement?
- Yes.

408
00:24:00,610 --> 00:24:03,710
And I'll do everything
I can to make sure...

409
00:24:03,810 --> 00:24:06,080
you get the payout
from our insurance policy.

410
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:10,550
Considering how Dad died,
I really shouldn't be taking this money.

411
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:15,490
But at least this money will keep us
from being thrown out of our shop.

412
00:24:15,860 --> 00:24:17,290
It'll give us some breathing room.

413
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:21,030
I don't know how this will sound,

414
00:24:21,970 --> 00:24:24,430
but I'm sure your father would understand.

415
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:27,170
Please, think of it as doing
what's best for your family.

416
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,140
Please accept it.

417
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:33,180
I'll sign the settlement papers.

418
00:24:34,110 --> 00:24:36,710
It's not like refusing to sign this
will bring my dad back.

419
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,180
Thank you.

420
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,880
And about what happened to your father...

421
00:24:41,380 --> 00:24:44,390
Once again, I am truly sorry.

422
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:03,610
Don't just stand there and sit down.

423
00:25:03,770 --> 00:25:06,840
- Let's just sit and eat.
- Chairman.

424
00:25:07,310 --> 00:25:08,510
Honey.

425
00:25:09,180 --> 00:25:11,150
Aren't we supposed
to have a wedding ceremony today?

426
00:25:11,650 --> 00:25:13,320
We're just going to eat here?

427
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:16,020
Not even a wedding venue,
let alone wedding photos?

428
00:25:16,620 --> 00:25:17,620
Seriously?

429
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:21,930
Then, what is all this?

430
00:25:22,260 --> 00:25:25,660
- It means you got ahead of yourself.
- Shut up!

431
00:25:25,730 --> 00:25:27,000
That's enough.

432
00:25:27,430 --> 00:25:30,700
A wedding ceremony at my age?
It'd be embarrassing.

433
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:34,000
A simple meal with family is enough.

434
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:36,010
But this is just wrong.

435
00:25:36,770 --> 00:25:38,740
I...

436
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:42,850
I was so excited,
thinking I'd be wearing a veil today.

437
00:25:43,050 --> 00:25:44,980
How could you blindside me like this?

438
00:25:47,350 --> 00:25:48,650
How could you do this to me?

439
00:25:59,630 --> 00:26:00,630
Mom!

440
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,040
Oh no.

441
00:26:05,570 --> 00:26:08,070
Are you okay? What are we going to do?

442
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:13,510
It's only been a few days
since you came here asking questions,

443
00:26:13,510 --> 00:26:14,880
and you're already at it again?

444
00:26:15,350 --> 00:26:18,110
You're making it look like
this hotel is a den of thieves.

445
00:26:19,050 --> 00:26:21,990
I was just passing by
and had a question for you.

446
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:29,760
(Case Summary, Yeongseo Police Chief)

447
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,500
What is this...

448
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:34,970
No, hold on a second.

449
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:44,770
He's the man who bought soju
near Jang Mi's father's accident scene.

450
00:26:45,710 --> 00:26:46,780
Do you recognize him?

451
00:26:46,780 --> 00:26:47,780
(Case Summary)

452
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:51,350
What kind of nonsense is that?
How would I know him?

453
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:52,980
Are you sure you don't recognize him?

454
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:08,430
- What? A composite sketch?
- He shoved it right in my face.

455
00:27:08,830 --> 00:27:10,600
And it looked like he knew it was me.

456
00:27:12,900 --> 00:27:14,040
No, that can't be.

457
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:18,040
There's no way they'd recognize you
from a sketch.

458
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:19,140
That's ridiculous.

459
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:22,050
- He was just testing you.
- Do you really think so?

460
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:25,720
You have nothing to worry about.

461
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:29,420
They're like cockroaches.

462
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:32,290
You get rid of one,
and another one just pops up.

463
00:27:33,260 --> 00:27:34,360
What a headache.

464
00:27:35,230 --> 00:27:37,360
I have to get rid of them
once and for all.

465
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:39,260
Manager Lee.

466
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:43,170
Can you think of a good way
to get rid of Oh Jang Mi?

467
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:49,040
Just how far is Mom willing to go?

468
00:27:49,740 --> 00:27:51,510
How can she say something so terrifying?

469
00:27:59,750 --> 00:28:02,250
How about we trade lives?

470
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:04,520
Seo Rin.

471
00:28:05,460 --> 00:28:06,690
Let's do it.

472
00:28:07,820 --> 00:28:11,290
I want to know
why you were separated from Mom...

473
00:28:12,230 --> 00:28:13,260
and ended up living there.

474
00:28:30,250 --> 00:28:31,710
(The First Man)

475
00:28:31,780 --> 00:28:34,450
There's just one difference between us.

476
00:28:34,450 --> 00:28:36,120
Since we're only switching for one day,

477
00:28:36,690 --> 00:28:38,220
you absolutely cannot get caught.

478
00:28:38,690 --> 00:28:42,660
Isn't something off with Seo Rin?
She seemed completely out of it.

479
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:45,960
That's strange.
Since when does she keep her room so tidy?

480
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,430
Remember.

481
00:28:47,730 --> 00:28:50,730
Don't act like you know or get involved.
You could get seriously hurt.

482
00:28:51,370 --> 00:28:54,340
Do you know who's responsible
for what happened to my mom?

483
00:28:56,470 --> 00:28:58,480
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
